args: The Empire's activity is becoming\nmore intense by the day.

The Divine Torch in particular is quite the
thorn in our side; if they have their way,
every village and town in the area will
be reduced to ash.
But given their mastery of fire mana, it is\ntoo dangerous to take them on directly.
Perhaps you would be willing\nto entrust this task to me?
Why, ya got some bright idea\nwhat we don't know about?
I do indeed: We will use me as bait\nto entice the Divine Torch.
Please, just listen to my plan...
We'll reach our next target before long.\nThey'll know the true extent of our power!
We will purify with glorious flame\nall who dare stand in our path!
You will do nothing of the sort!
This time, you and your flames will\nend by my hand!
You would take us on alone?\nSuch bravery is praiseworthy!
Very well! We shall use your burning\ncorpse as a bonfire to light the way\ninto our next glorious conflict!
Alone or no, I WILL stop you. Yaaah!
I almost admire her recklessness...\nNow go, men! Set her to burn!
It seems you are not the warrior I thought,\nfor you attack with naught but the basest\nof sentimentality!
Don't let her escape! Strike her down!
Clever girl... You thought to lure us to\na location with a great deal of water\nso as to keep our fires in check, eh?
Alas for you, for it will take more than\nwater to quench the power of OUR flame!
You might want to look down.
But why are only WE sinking?!\nHow do you continue to stand there?!
...We will lure the enemy to the bog\nand trap them there.
I learned something from the boy\nwho went to get herbs for me.
A number of locations in that bog\nare much deeper than they appear.
Like quicksand! Or, uh, a sinky pit?\n...Yeah, I dunno whatcha call it,\nbut it's a damn good idea.
The adults from the village know the bog\nlike the back of their hand, and can tell\nus which areas to avoid.
Which means we can move in safely.
The Divine Torch has bested me once;\nlet us use that confidence against them!
You dastards torched the villages,\nthe woods, and everything in between,\nand now you're gonna pay!
Strike back, you damned fools!\nBurn them to ash!
W-we can't! We're stuck fast,\nand so are our weapons!
N-no! This cannot be happening!\nWe are the Divine Torch! We... Noooo!
Looks like the Divine Torch has been...\nsnuffed out. OOOOOH YEAAAAAH!
Your plan was perfect, Fjorm!\nThey bought it hook, line, and sinker.
Now the villagers who fled will\nbe able to return to their homes.
This is all because you heard my idea\nand helped me execute it to perfection.
Today's victory belongs to you, Princess.
I am happy to have played even a small\npart, and will think back fondly on this\nday when I return to my own world.
It's a day all of us will remember.
Just as we'll remember Princess Fjorm,\nour steadfast ally and friend.
I'm truly glad I was able to meet you all.
